            ," in numbers. I had seen the prisoner in Mr. Edmonds's service; on the 25th of September he came to my shop, and said,</p>
               <p>"I have come from Mr. Edmonds for four dozen numbers of Lazarillo de Tormas;" I delivered to him fifty-two numbers, in consequence of that representation, and about the 15th of December I discovered this.</p>
